CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 7, 1964, pg. 11 reads: "Honored At LBJ Rally - A special citation was given to June Davis (center) at the Civic Arena, last week, when President Lyndon B. Johnson appeared there for a political rally. Miss Davis was cited for having contributed more than 40 hours of volunteer work in drive to register voters here.  Congratulating her are (left to right) Congressman William Moorhead, Mayor Joseph Barr and Magistrate Harry B. Fitzgerald, Democratic chairman of the Fifth Ward. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Congressman William Moorehead, June McCane Davis shaking hands with Pittsburgh Mayor Joseph M. Barr, and Alderman Harry Fitzgerald, standing in front of stage decorated with Lyndon Johnson presidential campaign materials
